execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/beltrami-deficit-truncation-survival.md:78:**Corrected framing:** "For exact Beltrami DNS flows, the truncation u_below shows geometrically decaying Beltrami deficit B_k ~ 0.56 * 2^{-k}, which is a trivial consequence of smooth truncation on smooth functions. However, (a) exact Beltrami is trivially regular, (b) near-Beltrami behavior is uncharacterized, (c) div(u_below) != 0 complicates the pressure interpretation, and (d) the connection to improved beta is not established." Grade: C+ (interesting computation, significant caveats). **This is the weakest claim in Strategy-001.**
