runtime/logs/codex-atlas-far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole-strategy-001-explorer-002.log:1449:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-atlas-far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole-strategy-001-strategizer.log:6383:execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/beta-current-value-four-thirds.md:71:S2-E007 adversarial review stress-tested the entire S2 obstruction result: (1) 15-paper literature search found no published improvement, with Vasseur (2025, arXiv:2503.02575) confirming the barrier; (2) all 7 closure arguments withstand attack — weakest is Route 1 (modified functional, speculative only); (3) all 3 combination attacks fail for structural reasons (tight interlocking of truncation, Sobolev, Chebyshev); (4) Tao (2016) independently explains why generic methods cannot resolve NS regularity. Novel claims ranked: seven-route obstruction (Claim 3) most significant at 8/10 novelty + 8/10 significance; Claims 1-4 combined publishable as "On the sharpness of the De Giorgi exponent beta = 4/3 for 3D Navier-Stokes." SDP formalization identified as most actionable next step for upgrading informal sharpness to rigorous. Full analysis in `s2-adversarial-review-beta-four-thirds.md`.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole-strategy-001-explorer-002.log:1450:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-atlas-far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole-strategy-001-strategizer.log:6417:execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/s2-adversarial-review-beta-four-thirds.md:23:Tao (2016, JAMS) shows that any proof of global regularity must use the *specific algebraic structure* of the NS nonlinearity — generic methods like De Giorgi iteration on the energy inequality cannot suffice. This independently explains why beta = 4/3 is stuck: the De Giorgi framework uses only energy-level structural information (Sobolev, Chebyshev, CZ), not the specific NS nonlinearity beyond its quadratic structure.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole-strategy-001-explorer-002.log:1451:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-atlas-far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole-strategy-001-strategizer.log:6533:execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/post-2007-beta-landscape.md:45:**Tao (2016, JAMS) connection:** Shows that blowup can occur for "averaged NS" — proving that any regularity proof must use the *specific algebraic structure* of the NS nonlinearity. Generic methods like De Giorgi iteration (which use only energy-level properties + quadratic structure) cannot suffice for full regularity. This independently explains the 4/3 barrier from a different angle.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole-strategy-001-explorer-002.log:1452:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-atlas-far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole-strategy-001-strategizer.log:6576:execution/instances/vasseur-pressure/strategies/strategy-002/explorations/exploration-007/REPORT.md:40:**Tao (2016) is especially relevant:** Shows that any proof of global regularity must use the *specific algebraic structure* of the NS nonlinearity — generic methods like De Giorgi iteration on the energy inequality cannot suffice. This implicitly explains why β = 4/3 is stuck.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole-strategy-001-explorer-002.log:1453:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-atlas-far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole-strategy-001-strategizer.log:6593:execution/instances/vasseur-pressure/strategies/strategy-002/explorations/exploration-006/code/literature_survey.md:186:2. The pressure is split into a **harmonic part** p_h (satisfying Delta p_h = 0 locally, hence smooth) and a **particular part** p_0 (determined by the nonlinearity). The harmonic part can be estimated by mean-value properties without CZ. The particular part is estimated using only local Sobolev inequalities on a ball, not global CZ theory.
