runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall-strategy-001-curator-003.log:1203:- **thermal-time strategy-001 meta-exploration-003** — The local vs. global modular flow question (does TTH apply K_A for subsystem A, or K_AB for the full system?) was not explicitly resolved until exploration-003. Explorations 001 and 002 implicitly assumed the local interpretation (K_A) and computed its consequences. Exploration-003 discovered that the global interpretation (K_AB) is trivially equivalent to standard QM. The strategizer note: "The literature disambiguation question (local vs. global) should have been in exploration-002 or even exploration-001. We spent two explorations computing assuming the local interpretation without confirming it was Connes-Rovelli's intent."
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall-strategy-001-curator-003.log:1221:- **riemann-hypothesis strategy-001 exploration 006** — The strategizer noted in retrospect: "Real symmetric matrices can only reach GOE (β=1), never GUE (β=2). This is a fundamental constraint I should have mentioned in the goal." The exploration was not wasted (it confirmed the constraints empirically), but a cleaner goal would have pre-scoped the search to complex-valued constructions from the start.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall-strategy-001-curator-003.log:1805:- **allow-explorer-synthesis.md** — Don't over-specify conclusions; specify what to investigate and what format to produce, but leave synthesis conclusions open. Explorers can discover structural patterns (e.g., two-tier tree-vs-loop insight; N²/p ≈ 250-310 ratio; underexploited constraints insight; unexpected no-go theorems) the strategizer didn't anticipate — often the most valuable outputs. **NEW variant: "What would be a breakthrough?" primes explorer for high-value output** without specifying what the answer should be. **NEW variant: "Explain WHY this agrees with [prior result]" elicits novel bonus derivations** — the mechanism explanation is more valuable than the consistency check itself (SED s003-meta-001: symmetry argument from P&C consistency check).
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall-strategy-001-curator-003.log:1816:- **verify-goal-claims-before-delegating.md** — **[NEW, YM s003-meta-005/s003-007]** Before writing GOAL.md citing a prior result (e.g., "M(Q) ≼ M(I) confirmed by E004"), verify the cited claim actually matches what the exploration found. Two-level fix: (1) strategizer re-reads REPORT.md before citing; (2) GOAL.md includes "first compute X for 3-5 random examples — if it fails, pivot." Prevented two wasted explorations in yang-mills s003. **NEW variant: "verify paper existence before citing"** [vasseur-pressure E003 — "Tran-Yu (2014, AIHP)" doesn't exist; actual program is 5 papers 2015-2021]. Distinct from preload-context (providing findings) and include-trivial-control-checks (validating code).
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall-strategy-001-curator-003.log:1925:- **compton-unruh strategy-001 exploration 001** — The Compton-Unruh resonance hypothesis failed by 43 orders of magnitude. This is not a "maybe with corrections" situation — it's a fundamental dimensional mismatch. The strategizer correctly identified the Gibbons-Hawking crossover (which IS at the right scale) as the pivot point for future work.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall-strategy-001-curator-003.log:1941:**Implication for strategizers:** When a negative result eliminates a direction, explicitly mark it as such in the strategy state and redirect budget. One exploration that kills a direction is worth more than three that make incremental progress.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall-strategy-001-curator-003.log:2430:- **allow-explorer-synthesis.md** — Don't over-specify conclusions; specify what to investigate and what format to produce, but leave synthesis conclusions open. Explorers can discover structural patterns (e.g., two-tier tree-vs-loop insight; N²/p ≈ 250-310 ratio; underexploited constraints insight; unexpected no-go theorems) the strategizer didn't anticipate — often the most valuable outputs. **NEW variant: "What would be a breakthrough?" primes explorer for high-value output** without specifying what the answer should be. **NEW variant: "Explain WHY this agrees with [prior result]" elicits novel bonus derivations** — the mechanism explanation is more valuable than the consistency check itself (SED s003-meta-001: symmetry argument from P&C consistency check).
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall-strategy-001-curator-003.log:2441:- **verify-goal-claims-before-delegating.md** — **[NEW, YM s003-meta-005/s003-007]** Before writing GOAL.md citing a prior result (e.g., "M(Q) ≼ M(I) confirmed by E004"), verify the cited claim actually matches what the exploration found. Two-level fix: (1) strategizer re-reads REPORT.md before citing; (2) GOAL.md includes "first compute X for 3-5 random examples — if it fails, pivot." Prevented two wasted explorations in yang-mills s003. **NEW variant: "verify paper existence before citing"** [vasseur-pressure E003 — "Tran-Yu (2014, AIHP)" doesn't exist; actual program is 5 papers 2015-2021]. Distinct from preload-context (providing findings) and include-trivial-control-checks (validating code).
