runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall-strategy-001-strategizer.log:3484:execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-003-thermal-time-learnings.md:40:- **Finishing strategies should be tight and fully mandatory.** Budget exactly N explorations, make all mandatory, say "strategy is not complete until all N have run." This prevents the strategizer from stopping early.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall-strategy-001-strategizer.log:3486:execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-001-thermal-time-learnings.md:22:2. **Phased approach with clear completion criteria was effective.** The strategizer knew when Phase 1 was done (modular Hamiltonians computed, normalization resolved) and transitioned cleanly to Phase 2. The criteria prevented both premature and excessive exploration.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall-strategy-001-strategizer.log:3495:execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-002-thermal-time-learnings.md:44:- **Early stopping by strategizers is a mixed signal.** Strategy-002 stopped at 3/10 explorations. The results were genuinely decisive — but the remaining work (adversarial, coherent test) would have strengthened the claims significantly. Missionaries should either (a) budget tighter (5 explorations, all mandatory) to prevent premature stopping, or (b) include an explicit "minimum exploration count" rule.
