runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall-strategy-001-strategizer.log:22970: slug: strategizer
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall-strategy-001-strategizer.log:23916:execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/check-faithful-support-shrinkage-before-narrowing.md:32:Narrowing can create fake progress. A mission that sounds smaller may still require the entire old object once words like "trigger," "delay," "witness," or "small compared to" are made exact. If the faithful support has not shrunk, the strategizer should spend the turn transferring prior negatives, not pretending a new Phase 1 object exists.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall-strategy-001-strategizer.log:23927:execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-001-vasseur-pressure-learnings.md:20:E009 (adversarial review) correctly identified Claim 5 as the weakest link. E010 (targeted test) definitively showed the Beltrami mechanism doesn't generalize. Without this sequence, the final report would have overclaimed the Beltrami connection. **Always budget at least 1 exploration after the adversarial review for targeted follow-up on the weakest identified claim.** This should be prescribed in the methodology, not left to strategizer judgment.
