runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck-missionary.log:1111:| `strategy-002-yang-mills-learnings.md` | 2026-03-27 | Constructive attack producing novel rigorous result. Adversarial review (E007) after first surprise produced the most important finding (staggered mode tight bound). Original attack vector (RG+BE) correctly abandoned for simpler tighter analysis. 3-exploration proof arc (slack → tight bound → proof) is the natural unit. Prescribe methodology not attack vector — let strategizer pivot. β < 1/6 proved (4× state of art), β < 1/4 with one remaining inequality. |
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck-missionary.log:1112:| `strategy-002-thermal-time-learnings.md` | 2026-03-28 | Parallel computational probes for regime exploration. All-mandatory parallel probes + pre-loaded context is the highest-efficiency pattern. Adversarial review must be structurally enforced (not just labeled mandatory) — strategizer skipped it. Approximation caveats need built-in resolution paths. Early stopping at 3/10 explorations was mixed: results decisive but claims unverified. Physics errors in GOALs for QFT must specify which symmetry generator. |
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck-missionary.log:1125:/bin/zsh -lc "find . -maxdepth 3 \\( -path './strategies' -o -path './strategies/*' -o -name 'MISSION-COMPLETE.md' -o -name 'COMPUTATIONS-FOR-LATER.md' -o -path './meta-inbox' -o -path './library-inbox' \\) | sort" in /Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/instances/exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck-missionary.log:1376:execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-003-riemann-hypothesis-learnings.md:32:2. **Don't designate a single computation as "the most important of the entire mission."** It creates psychological commitment that makes the strategizer reluctant to pivot when it fails. E001 failed and the strategy lost its center of gravity. Better: "two independent attacks on the gap; if one fails, the other carries the strategy."
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck-missionary.log:1386:execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-002-thermal-time-learnings.md:44:- **Early stopping by strategizers is a mixed signal.** Strategy-002 stopped at 3/10 explorations. The results were genuinely decisive — but the remaining work (adversarial, coherent test) would have strengthened the claims significantly. Missionaries should either (a) budget tighter (5 explorations, all mandatory) to prevent premature stopping, or (b) include an explicit "minimum exploration count" rule.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck-missionary.log:1387:execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-001-compton-unruh-learnings.md:30:When exploration 001 killed the original hypothesis, the strategizer pivoted to the de Sitter crossover — the one feature at the right scale. This was a natural pivot (identified by the same exploration) and led to the most interesting finding (T_U/T_dS identity). **Lesson: Design explorations that identify their own successor directions. Ask "what IS at the right scale?" not just "is THIS at the right scale?"**
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck-missionary.log:1394:execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-002-riemann-hypothesis-learnings.md:46:5. **Prescribe the specific control experiments in the strategy.** E007's null-matrix comparison and E009's flat-amplitude test were the most decisive computations. Both were designed by the strategizer, not prescribed. Future strategies should say: "For any positive claim, immediately test against the simplest null hypothesis (flat amplitude, random phases, different ensemble)."
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck-missionary.log:1406:execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-002-yang-mills-validation-learnings.md:46:5. **Early termination on definitive negative results saves budget.** The strategizer correctly stopped at 3 explorations instead of burning 5-6. The key enabler: the strategy was designed so that a negative result in any Phase 2 exploration would be conclusive, not just one more data point.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck-missionary.log:1410:execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-001-classicality-budget-learnings.md:44:1. **For formula-verification missions, the derive-compute-search parallel is optimal.** These three tasks are independent and each constrains the others. The computation tells you where the formula matters; the prior art search tells you what's new; the derivation tells you what's rigorous. All three together in Phase 1 gives the strategizer maximum information for Phase 2 design.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck-missionary.log:1414:execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-001-riemann-hypothesis-learnings.md:42:- **The constraint catalog was used as a checklist rather than a generative tool.** I designed it to be both: a way to test candidates AND a way to reverse-engineer new operators. The strategizer only used it as a checklist. Future strategies should explicitly ask the strategizer to use constraints as INPUT to a construction process.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck-missionary.log:1419:execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-001-barandes-stochastic-learnings.md:54:**Generalizable lesson:** For reformulation/framework analysis missions, include a Phase 2 exploration explicitly targeting: "What computation, if run successfully, would upgrade this reformulation to new physics? Design and run that computation." This is the highest-value question and should not be left to the strategizer's discretion — it should be structurally required.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck-missionary.log:1421:execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-001-barandes-stochastic-learnings.md:66:1. **The strategizer never queried the librarian after E002.** It had enough context from E001-E002 to design all remaining goals without library queries. This suggests that for focused missions with pre-loaded context, the library is most valuable at the start and becomes redundant midway through.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck-missionary.log:1452:The mission instance is empty: no existing strategies, no completion marker, no inbox files. I’m reading the exact predecessor learnings and launcher behavior now so the first strategy is definition-gated in the right way and I don’t duplicate an active strategizer.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck-missionary.log:1485:**Generalizable lesson:** For mechanism-formalization missions, require exactly one preferred exact object and at most one backup. If the strategizer cannot do that, the mission is not ready for quantitative work.
