runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-strategy-001-strategizer.log:28611:- **allow-explorer-synthesis.md** — Don't over-specify conclusions; specify what to investigate and what format to produce, but leave synthesis conclusions open. Explorers can discover structural patterns (e.g., two-tier tree-vs-loop insight; N²/p ≈ 250-310 ratio; underexploited constraints insight; unexpected no-go theorems) the strategizer didn't anticipate — often the most valuable outputs. **NEW variant: "What would be a breakthrough?" primes explorer for high-value output** without specifying what the answer should be. **NEW variant: "Explain WHY this agrees with [prior result]" elicits novel bonus derivations** — the mechanism explanation is more valuable than the consistency check itself (SED s003-meta-001: symmetry argument from P&C consistency check).
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-strategy-001-strategizer.log:28622:- **verify-goal-claims-before-delegating.md** — **[NEW, YM s003-meta-005/s003-007]** Before writing GOAL.md citing a prior result (e.g., "M(Q) ≼ M(I) confirmed by E004"), verify the cited claim actually matches what the exploration found. Two-level fix: (1) strategizer re-reads REPORT.md before citing; (2) GOAL.md includes "first compute X for 3-5 random examples — if it fails, pivot." Prevented two wasted explorations in yang-mills s003. **NEW variant: "verify paper existence before citing"** [vasseur-pressure E003 — "Tran-Yu (2014, AIHP)" doesn't exist; actual program is 5 papers 2015-2021]. Distinct from preload-context (providing findings) and include-trivial-control-checks (validating code).
