runtime/logs/codex-atlas-anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall-strategy-001-curator-001.log:1125:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/allow-explorer-synthesis.md:10:Don't over-specify the conclusions you want explorers to reach. Goals should specify WHAT to investigate and WHAT FORMAT to produce, but leave the synthesis conclusions open. Explorers can identify structural patterns the strategizer didn't anticipate — these are often the most valuable outputs.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall-strategy-001-curator-001.log:1126:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/allow-explorer-synthesis.md:40:**Design template:** When you expect a result to be consistent with prior work, add to the goal: "Check consistency with [prior result]. **Explain WHY they agree or disagree at the level of mechanism — not just the fact of agreement.**" This triggers the explorer to work through the algebra and often produces a novel structural insight the strategizer didn't anticipate.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall-strategy-001-curator-001.log:1131:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:26:- **allow-explorer-synthesis.md** — Don't over-specify conclusions; specify what to investigate and what format to produce, but leave synthesis conclusions open. Explorers can discover structural patterns (e.g., two-tier tree-vs-loop insight; N²/p ≈ 250-310 ratio; underexploited constraints insight; unexpected no-go theorems) the strategizer didn't anticipate — often the most valuable outputs. **NEW variant: "What would be a breakthrough?" primes explorer for high-value output** without specifying what the answer should be. **NEW variant: "Explain WHY this agrees with [prior result]" elicits novel bonus derivations** — the mechanism explanation is more valuable than the consistency check itself (SED s003-meta-001: symmetry argument from P&C consistency check).
