runtime/logs/codex-atlas-anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall-strategy-001-curator-001.log:1846:- **verify-goal-claims-before-delegating.md** — **[NEW, YM s003-meta-005/s003-007]** Before writing GOAL.md citing a prior result (e.g., "M(Q) ≼ M(I) confirmed by E004"), verify the cited claim actually matches what the exploration found. Two-level fix: (1) strategizer re-reads REPORT.md before citing; (2) GOAL.md includes "first compute X for 3-5 random examples — if it fails, pivot." Prevented two wasted explorations in yang-mills s003. **NEW variant: "verify paper existence before citing"** [vasseur-pressure E003 — "Tran-Yu (2014, AIHP)" doesn't exist; actual program is 5 papers 2015-2021]. Distinct from preload-context (providing findings) and include-trivial-control-checks (validating code).
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall-strategy-001-curator-001.log:1932:- **check-bypass-not-just-improve-bottleneck.md** — NEW (vasseur-pressure S2-E005): When a bottleneck tool limits progress, always ask "can we avoid this tool entirely?" before "can we improve it?" Protocol: (1) Can we avoid using this tool at all? (2) Is there a fundamentally different tool for the same job? (3) Can we improve the tool's output? S2-E001 through S2-E005 spent 5 explorations on question 3 (improving CZ or working around it); the strategizer should have asked question 1 after S2-E001 showed all CZ-based routes are tight. Distinct from ask-what-replaces-the-bottleneck (what new bottleneck after reformulation vs. whether to use the tool at all), decomposition-audit-before-attacking-barrier (which step is tight vs. whether the framework is right), and decisive-negative-pivot (when to stop vs. what direction to go).
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-tiny-trigger-firewall-strategy-001-explorer-001.log:1190:**Generalizable lesson:** For mechanism-formalization missions, require exactly one preferred exact object and at most one backup. If the strategizer cannot do that, the mission is not ready for quantitative work.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-tiny-trigger-firewall-strategy-001-explorer-001.log:1398:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/runtime/results/codex-atlas-anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall-strategy-001-strategizer.md:3:Bottom line: the strategy reached a mechanism-level negative result. Tao’s blowup mechanism was reconstructed sharply as a five-mode delayed-threshold circuit, and the intervention map narrowed the live discrepancy to exact-NS circuit non-isolability, but that candidate never sharpened into a concrete firewall object rather than a qualitative statement about interaction entanglement.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-tiny-trigger-firewall-strategy-001-explorer-001.log:1694:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-002-yang-mills-learnings.md:26:1. **Don't prescribe the specific attack vector; prescribe the methodology for finding one.** I prescribed "test the RG+Bakry-Émery combination." The strategizer correctly ignored this when it found something better (Hessian sharpness). The strategy should have said: "Your objective is to extend the mass gap threshold. Start by understanding what limits the current threshold, then attack the biggest source of slack." This is more general and would have led to the same result.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-tiny-trigger-firewall-strategy-001-explorer-001.log:1706:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/adversarial-synthesis-goal-structure.md:71:**[vasseur-pressure S2-E007]** Adversarial reviews should propose the most actionable formalization step for informal claims, not just identify weaknesses. "This claim needs work" produces paralysis; "here's how to make it rigorous" enables action. S2-E007: identifying the SDP approach (sum-of-squares relaxation to find optimal |{|u| > lambda}| bound given NS constraints) as the specific formalization path for the informal sharpness claim was the most actionable output of the entire adversarial review. Protocol: for each claim rated below VERIFIED, propose one specific formalization method (SDP, counterexample search, formal definition, etc.) with enough detail that the strategizer can write a GOAL.md.
