runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-tiny-trigger-firewall-strategy-001-curator-001.log:1751:- **compton-unruh strategy-001 exploration 001** — The Compton-Unruh resonance hypothesis failed by 43 orders of magnitude. This is not a "maybe with corrections" situation — it's a fundamental dimensional mismatch. The strategizer correctly identified the Gibbons-Hawking crossover (which IS at the right scale) as the pivot point for future work.
runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-tiny-trigger-firewall-strategy-001-curator-001.log:1767:**Implication for strategizers:** When a negative result eliminates a direction, explicitly mark it as such in the strategy state and redirect budget. One exploration that kills a direction is worth more than three that make incremental progress.
