+# Strategy 001: Freeze One Helical Packet Object, Then Force or Kill the Bottleneck
+
+## Objective
+
+Turn the mission's surviving clue
+
+```text
+low exact-ledger leakage seems to favor global near-homochirality,
+while the load-bearing Tao-like activation edge appears obligatorily heterochiral
+```
+
+into one theorem-facing exact-NS packet question and drive it to one of the mission's named outcomes:
+
+1. positive helical bottleneck,
+2. counterexample: low-leakage low-sign-defect packet realization exists,
+3. canonicity failure,
+4. model-level failure: the singleton sign clue does not survive packet lift.
+
+This strategy is not allowed to drift back into singleton exact-mode work, broad Tao surveys, or packet engineering that changes the object while testing it.
+
+## Methodology
+
+### Phase 0: Canonical Packet-Object Gate
+
+Start from the best existing packet-level exact object for Tao-like roles and freeze one preferred helical packet model, with at most one backup only if it is genuinely inequivalent.
+
+The preferred object must specify explicitly:
+
+- one fixed packet family for the five Tao-like roles,
+- one fixed support / refinement convention,
+- one fixed conjugate-pair representative rule or quotient convention,
+- one fixed desired Tao-like role graph,
+- one fixed exact-ledger leakage functional `Leak(I)`,
+- one fixed global sign-coherence functional `SD_part(I)`,
+- one fixed desired-edge heterochirality functional `SD_target(I)`,
+- one fixed activation-window convention,
+- one exact-vs-tolerance ledger separating NS data from user-chosen parameters.
+
+The object is admissible only if the above items do not move under harmless packet refinements, representative relabelings, or equivalent bookkeeping choices.
+
+Required deliverables:
+
+- one preferred packet/sign object and at most one backup,
+- a short notation table,
+- one canonicity checklist covering support, representatives, desired-edge bookkeeping, and leakage scalarization,
+- a precise statement of what would count as positive bottleneck, counterexample, canonicity failure, or model-level failure.
+
+Phase 0 kill conditions:
+
+- If the packet support, role graph, leakage budget, or sign functionals change under admissible refinements, stop with `canonicity failure`.
+- If the sign functionals depend on arbitrary representative choices with no defensible quotient rule, stop with `canonicity failure`.
+- If the only surviving object is just a repackaged version of the already-failed clustered exact-mode packet family, stop sharply rather than relabeling it as progress.
+
+### Phase 1: Exact-Ledger Packet Sign Computation
+
+Attack the frozen preferred object directly in exact NS helical-triad bookkeeping.
+
+This phase must compute or tightly analyze at least one nontrivial relation among
+
+```text
+(Leak(I), SD_part(I), SD_target(I)).
+```
+
+Every exploration in this phase must begin with one concrete target such as:
+
+- `Leak(I) <= eps` implies `SD_part(I) <= delta(eps)`,
+- every admissible desired-drive window has `SD_target(I) >= c > 0`,
+- the three quantities cannot simultaneously be small,
+- or one explicit low-leakage candidate with both low global sign defect and low target-edge heterochirality defect.
+
+Required deliverables:
+
+- one quantitative table, inequality, incompatibility statement, or explicit candidate configuration on the chosen packet object,
+- an exact-fidelity note stating which exact NS structures are preserved and which, if any, are reduced,
+- a statement of whether the singleton sign clue survives, weakens, or disappears under the packet lift.
+
+Phase 1 kill condition:
+
+- If the singleton sign signal disappears on the frozen faithful packet object, stop with `model-level failure`.
+
+### Phase 2: Sharp Bottleneck or Counterexample Formulation
+
+Promote the best surviving Phase 1 relation into one theorem candidate or one counterexample target.
+
+Preferred theorem shapes:
+
+- `Leak(I) <= eps0` forces `SD_part(I) <= delta(eps0)`,
+- every Tao-like activation window has `SD_target(I) >= c1 > 0`,
+- the triple `(Leak, SD_part, SD_target)` cannot be simultaneously small.
+
+Preferred counterexample shape:
+
+- one canonical packet object admits a low-leakage Tao-like realization with both low global minority-helicity participation and low desired-edge heterochirality defect.
+
+This phase must state the target theorem or counterexample before derivations or computations. Do not substitute qualitative language about homochiral versus heterochiral tendencies for a quantitative claim.
+
+### Phase 3: Mandatory Adversarial Helical Stress Test
+
+Any apparent bottleneck or counterexample must be attacked adversarially.
+
+The adversarial pass must specifically try to break the result by testing:
+
+- near-homochiral packet families designed to minimize spectator leakage,
+- mixed-sign target edges with unusually low global sign defect,
+- packet refinements or representative changes that threaten canonicity,
+- symmetry choices that trivialize `SD_part` or `SD_target`,
+- configurations that keep the desired Tao-like edge alive while shifting leakage into supposedly harmless terms.
+
+If the positive bottleneck only survives by changing the packet object, record `canonicity failure`, not success.
+If the counterexample only survives in a reduced model that no longer carries the exact NS helical ledger faithfully, record `model-level failure`, not success.
+
+### Phase 4: Final Verdict
+
+Finish with exactly one named mission outcome:
+
+1. positive helical bottleneck,
+2. counterexample: low-leakage low-sign-defect packet realization exists,
+3. canonicity failure,
+4. model-level failure: singleton sign clue does not survive packet lift.
+
+The final report must make the recommendation unambiguous:
+
+- pursue as a real theorem-facing obstruction,
+- kill as a counterexample,
+- or stop because the object itself never stabilized canonically.
+
+## Cross-Phase Rules
+
+1. By the end of Phase 0 there must be one preferred packet/sign object and at most one backup.
+2. One theorem target or one counterexample target per exploration. State it before derivations.
+3. Exact-NS fidelity is non-negotiable. Any reduction must list preserved and discarded exact structures explicitly.
+4. Do not collapse `Leak`, `SD_part`, and `SD_target` into one scalar at the start. Keep the pair of sign quantities visible unless a later theorem genuinely justifies compression.
+5. Global sign coherence must be computed on a fixed conjugate-pair representative quotient or equally canonical equivalent. Raw counting on the full sign-closed support is not admissible because it trivializes the sign balance.
+6. Treat the first failed clustered exact-mode packet model as prior negative evidence, not as an unexplored baseline to rebuild casually.
+7. Run canonicity and static-object checks before coefficient optimization or minimization campaigns.
+8. Do not accept "homochiral tends to inverse transfer" or similar helical folklore as evidence. Every accepted claim must point to the chosen exact packet ledger.
+9. Every substantial claim in the final report must be tagged `[VERIFIED]`, `[COMPUTED]`, `[CHECKED]`, or `[CONJECTURED]`.
+10. Maintain a Direction Status Tracker in `REASONING.md` using `OPEN / PROMISING / CLOSED / EXHAUSTED`.
+11. Do not reopen De Giorgi, epsilon-regularity, pressure, host-space, or generic singleton exact-circuit routes under new names.
+12. Early stopping is correct if canonicity fails cleanly, the packet lift kills the singleton signal cleanly, or a quantitative obstruction/counterexample survives adversarial review.
+
+## Validation Criteria
+
+This strategy succeeds if it delivers all of:
+
+- one frozen packet/sign object narrow enough to be true or false,
+- sign and leakage functionals that are canonical enough that failure would still be meaningful,
+- at least one quantitative relation among `Leak`, `SD_part`, and `SD_target`,
+- a mandatory adversarial helical stress test,
+- an unambiguous terminal verdict in one of the mission's named outcomes.
+
+This strategy is exhausted if:
+
+- the packet object fails canonization cleanly,
+- the singleton sign clue dies under the faithful packet lift,
+- a positive bottleneck or counterexample survives adversarial review,
+- or the only remaining uncertainty is a sharper next-strategy question rather than more packet-definition drift.
+
+## Context
+
+### Predecessor results to preload
+
+- `execution/instances/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/MISSION-COMPLETE.md`
+  - The preferred singleton exact Tao-circuit object is structurally impossible.
+  - Packetized backups failed because support, projection, leakage scalarization, and restoration conventions were not canonical.
+- `execution/instances/exact-ns-tiny-trigger-firewall/MISSION-COMPLETE.md`
+  - Narrowing to the trigger alone did not create a new canonical faithful object.
+  - Packetized trigger backups inherited the same canonization failure.
+- `execution/instances/exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall/MISSION-COMPLETE.md`
+  - Bypassing packets by changing object class worked for definition, but the precursor theorem failed structurally.
+  - This matters here because the present mission intentionally reopens the packet branch and must therefore clear the packet-object gate honestly.
+- `execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-001-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-learnings.md`
+  - Definition-gated missions need one preferred object, smallest-support audits before downstream optimization, and immediate stopping when backups are non-canonical.
+- `execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/exact-helical-near-closed-tao-circuit-definition.md`
+  - The exact helical ledger and desired-vs-leakage split are already the right bookkeeping language.
+- `execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/packetized-tao-circuit-noncanonical.md`
+  - Packetization is not automatically progress; canonization is the first gate.
+- `execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/exact-ns-triadic-coefficient-rigidity.md`
+  - Tao-like gate strengths are not free parameters in exact NS.
+- `execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/exact-ns-unavoidable-spectator-couplings.md`
+  - Desired channels come with exact companion terms, so leakage accounting must stay exact-ledger based.
+
+### What is already closed
+
+- singleton exact-circuit embedding,
+- trigger-only narrowing as a fresh object,
+- packet missions that leave support, projection, or leakage bookkeeping underdefined,
+- physical-space precursor missions without built-in memory structure,
+- estimate-level or host-space reopenings.
+
+### Strategic aim
+
+The live question is not whether singleton exact modes work. They do not.
+
+The live question is:
+
+```text
+can one canonically freeze a packet-level exact NS helical ledger on which
+low leakage pushes the active packet family toward one-sign dominance while
+the load-bearing Tao-like edges still require heterochiral participation?
+```
+
+This strategy should answer that for one frozen object, not for a menu of packet variants.
+
+## Budget Guidance
+
+Target 4-6 explorations.
+
+Expected efficient path:
+
+- 1 exploration for the packet-object / canonicity gate,
+- 1 exploration for quantitative packet-level sign-functional computation,
+- 1 exploration for the main bottleneck theorem candidate or counterexample,
+- 1 exploration for adversarial helical stress testing,
+- optionally 1 targeted repair exploration only if the object survives canonization but one quantitative relation remains unresolved.
+
+Do not spend the budget widening the packet object. If the object moves, stop.

